            <p class="narrative">
                Nami managed to hold Luffy back for a moment. "Hold on, let's see what we're walking into." They watched from near the entrance. The Baratie was lively, filled with sailors, locals, and tourists. The smell of delicious food was almost overwhelming. They overheard snippets of conversation: "...heard Chef Sanji's seafood pasta makes you remember your first love...", "...Zeff runs a tight ship, but he's got a heart of gold...", "...Watch out for the 'Critique Pirates', they were sniffing around earlier..."
            </p>
             <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FFA500/FFFFFF?text=N" alt="Nami Icon" class="character-icon">"'Critique Pirates'? That sounds ominous. Maybe we should be cautious."</p>
             <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FF0000/FFFFFF?text=L" alt="Luffy Icon" class="character-icon"><span class="luffy-dialogue">Critics? Who cares! I wanna try that pasta story! Let's go!</span></p>
            <p class="narrative">Just then, a commotion erupted inside. A customer went flying out the door, propelled by a powerful kick from a blond chef with a cigarette.</p>
             <div class="character-intro">
                <strong><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/0000FF/FFFFFF?text=S" alt="Sanji Icon" class="character-icon">Character Introduced: Sanji</strong> - A passionate, fiery chef working at the Baratie. Reveres food and women, detests waste. His kicks are legendary amongst the staff.
