            <h2>Meeting the Fiery Chef</h2>
            <p class="narrative">
                Ignoring Nami's warnings (or Usopp's trembling), Luffy approached the blond chef, Sanji, who was lighting a new cigarette, looking thoroughly annoyed.
            </p>
             <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FF0000/FFFFFF?text=L" alt="Luffy Icon" class="character-icon"><span class="luffy-dialogue">That was amazing! Your food sounds amazing too! I'm Luffy, I'm gonna be the King of Storytellers! Can you join my crew and cook story-food?</span></p>
            <p class="narrative">
                Sanji blinked, smoke curling around his face. He looked Luffy up and down. Before he could answer, Zeff's gruff voice cut through the air. "Sanji! Less kicking, more cooking! And who are these brats?"
            </p>
            <p class="narrative">Just then, a group of people in sharp suits entered, led by a man with an arrogant smirk. "Well, well. The infamous Baratie Bistro. We are the Critique Pirates. Prepare for a thorough... *deconstruction*." The air grew tense.</p>
