         <div class="scene hidden" id="scene4_luffyDistraction">
             <h2>An Unexpected Tale</h2>
             <p class="narrative">Sensing the rising tension, Luffy suddenly jumped onto a table. <span class="luffy-dialogue">"HEY EVERYONE! WANNA HEAR A STORY?!"</span> His voice, brimming with energy, cut through the hostility. The Critique Pirates looked momentarily confused.</p>
             <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FFA500/FFFFFF?text=N" alt="Nami Icon" class="character-icon">"Luffy, now is not the time!"</p>
             <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FFFF00/000000?text=U" alt="Usopp Icon" class="character-icon">"Y-yeah! Unless... unless it's the story of Captain Usopp defeating fifty critics with a single word!"</p>
             <p class="narrative">Sanji raised an eyebrow, a flicker of amusement in his eyes. Zeff watched impassively. Fullbody scoffed, "A distraction? Pathetic."</p>
             <div class="action">
                 <button onclick="showScene('scene5_luffyStory')">Tell the story anyway! Capture their attention!</button>
                  <button onclick="showScene('scene5_teamUp')">Use the distraction to team up with Sanji verbally.</button>
             </div>
         </div>


        <!-- Scene 5 Climax -->
        <div class="scene hidden" id="scene5_luffyStory">
            <h2>The Power of Passion</h2>
            <p class="narrative">Luffy took a deep breath, grinned, and began. He didn't tell a polished epic, but a raw, energetic tale about freedom, friendship, and chasing dreams against all odds. He spoke of shared meals under starry skies, of overcoming impossible challenges with sheer willpower. As he spoke, fueled by the Baratie's unique 'Echo Isle' energy and the passion radiating from Sanji and Zeff, something happened.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Tiny, shimmering lights began to appear in the air around Luffy – <span class="story-spark">Story Sparks!</span> Faint at first, then brighter, more numerous. The diners gasped. Even the Critique Pirates faltered, momentarily stunned by the unexpected phenomenon.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Sanji stared, cigarette falling from his lips. He felt... something. A resonance. A reminder of his own hidden dream – the All Blue, a place where all the world's recipes could be found.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Luffy finished with a booming laugh. <span class="luffy-dialogue">"See?! Stories are AWESOME!"</span></p>
            <p class="narrative">Fullbody, unnerved by the Sparks, stammered, "Tricks! Cheap illusions!" But his voice lacked conviction. His crew looked uncertain.</p>
            <div class="action">
                 <button onclick="showScene('scene6_resolution')">Press the advantage! Drive the critics out!</button>
            </div>
        </div>

         <div class="scene hidden" id="scene5_teamUp">
            <h2>Words and Kicks</h2>
            <p class="narrative">Luffy's energy was infectious. Sanji, seeing Luffy's simple defense of passion, smirked. "He's right, you know. You wouldn't understand the soul of cooking if it kicked you in the face." He stepped forward, not physically attacking, but verbally dissecting the critics' cold logic with sharp, passionate arguments about flavor, memory, and the joy of eating.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Usopp, emboldened, launched into a wildly exaggerated tale of how *he* once debated a hundred critics into silence. Nami chimed in with cutting remarks about their lack of understanding of 'value'.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Luffy cheered them on. <span class="luffy-dialogue">"Yeah! Tell 'em! Shishishi!"</span> His sheer belief in his friends seemed to amplify their words. Small <span class="story-spark">Story Sparks</span> flickered around Sanji and Usopp as they spoke with genuine fervor.</p>
            <p class="narrative">The Critique Pirates, overwhelmed by the unexpected, passionate counter-attack and the strange lights, began to backpedal.</p>
             <div class="action">
                 <button onclick="showScene('scene6_resolution')">Drive the critics out!</button>
             </div>
         </div>


        <!-- Scene 6: Resolution -->
        <div class="scene hidden" id="scene6_resolution">
            <h2>A New Ally (and a Meal!)</h2>
            <p class="narrative">Whether through Luffy's story or the team's verbal barrage, the Critique Pirates were routed. They fled the Baratie amidst the cheers of the diners and staff, muttering about reporting this 'anomaly'.</p>
            <p class="narrative">Zeff let out a gruff chuckle. "Hmph. Not bad, brats."</p>
            <p class="narrative">Sanji walked over to Luffy, lighting another cigarette. He looked thoughtful. "Oi, storyteller. Your tales... they got guts. And you defended the kitchen's heart." He paused. "...You need a cook for your 'Story Crew'?"</p>
            <p><img src="https://via.placeholder.com/50/FF0000/FFFFFF?text=L" alt="Luffy Icon" class="character-icon"><span class="luffy-dialogue">YEAH! REALLY?! Awesome! Let's eat first! I'm starving! MEAT!</span></p>
            <p class="narrative">Sanji sighed, a small smile playing on his lips. "Fine. But Nami-swan eats first." He winked at a flustered Nami.</p>
            <p class="narrative">As Sanji disappeared into the kitchen, promising a meal that would tell its own story, Luffy beamed. They had faced their first challenge, defended an Echo Isle, and gained a powerful new ally. The journey to the One Tale felt a little closer.</p>
            <div class="character-intro">
